It is reported that unplanned absenteeism costs the country nearly R20bn per annum. CAPE TOWN - It's back to the grindstone for many today after Tuesday was declared a public holiday.The Cape Chamber of Commerce says the impact on the economy will be less than usual, because the manufacturing and building industries are closed over this period.President Jacob Zuma declared the 27 December a public holiday to compensate for Christmas Day falling on a Sunday.The chamber s Janine Myburgh says they hope the extra day will have a positive effect on unplanned absenteeism. Unplanned absenteeism, such as sick leave, is reported to cost the country nearly R20 billion per annum. Hopefully the extra holiday will alleviate that this some degree by providing positive work-life balance. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)